message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in North Korea in the past 20 years was the ascension of Kim Jong-un to power after the death of his father, Kim Jong-il, in 2011. This marked a generational change in leadership and solidified the third generation of the Kim family dynasty in North Korea. Kim Jong-un has since implemented several significant policies and carried out numerous nuclear and missile tests, significantly impacting the diplomatic landscape and the country's relationship with the international community.
